<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" box="[189,1182,266,293]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,313,266,292]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering from August to September; fruiting from October to December.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="283" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,302,328]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The specific epithet of our new species, “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Ren &amp; Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[850,988,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyalamensis">
<emphasis box="[850,988,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">nyalamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, is derived from the 
<typeStatus box="[1257,1305,303,329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
locality, i.e. Nyalam county in southern 
<collectingRegion box="[447,531,338,364]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Xizang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[542,613,338,364]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="283" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,489,374,400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Ren &amp; Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[524,754,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyalamensis">
<emphasis box="[524,754,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Synotis nyalamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[1158,1206,375,401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
locality, i.e. Nyalam county in southern 
<collectingRegion box="[353,437,410,436]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Xizang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[448,515,410,436]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[531,600,410,437]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2065,2087]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,1275,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-67@4.[164,1423,1275,2040]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of Synotis kunthiana (■) and S. nyalamensis sp. nov. (●)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). It grows in gravelly places on mountain slope at an altitude of ca. 
<quantity box="[1366,1451,410,437]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" unit="m" value="3200.0">3200 m</quantity>
above sea level. Its putative closest ally, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[585,751,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunthiana">
<emphasis box="[585,751,446,473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Syn. kunthiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is distributed only in northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1152,1212,446,472]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1293,446,472]" name="Nepal" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1349,1447,446,472]" name="Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, not in 
<collectingCountry box="[208,275,482,508]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[290,358,482,509]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2065,2087]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,1275,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-67@4.[164,1423,1275,2040]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of Synotis kunthiana (■) and S. nyalamensis sp. nov. (●)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6831542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6831542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,426,518,544]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Conservation status</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Ren &amp; Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[462,687,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyalamensis">
<emphasis box="[462,687,518,545]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Synotis nyalamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a locally endemic species. During our field work we tried our best to search for it around the 
<typeStatus box="[426,474,555,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">type</typeStatus>
locality but discovered only a small population with ca. 15 mature individuals. We have also been unable to trace any herbarium specimen of this species collected prior to us. According to IUCN Red List categories and criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[401,982,626,652]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" refId="ref2605" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria version 14 [EB / OL]. 2020 - 04 - 10. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. [https: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf]" type="url" year="2019">IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee 2019</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Ren &amp; Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1003,1196,626,653]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyalamensis">
<emphasis box="[1003,1196,626,653]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Syn. nyalamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be categorized as a Critically Endangered (CR) species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,256,698,724]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Notes</emphasis>
:—As pointed out by Jeffery &amp; Chen (1984), a notable feature of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Clarke" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[1135,1216,699,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1135,1216,699,725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Synotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the occurrence of closely similar, usually vicariant but sometimes partially sympatric sets of similar species, which on experimental study may prove better distinguished at subspecific rank. They gave eight examples in the Chinese flora. It seems that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[185,352,806,833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunthiana">
<emphasis box="[185,352,806,833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Syn. kunthiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Ren &amp; Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[407,600,806,833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyalamensis">
<emphasis box="[407,447,807,833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Syn</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[462,600,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">nyalamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are an example in the Himalayan flora. Morphologically these two species, although different in some characters, are indeed closely similar to each other (
<tableCitation box="[1019,1103,842,868]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,224,1096,1120]" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological comparison of Synotis kunthiana and S. nyalamensis." pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">
According to Jeffery &amp; Chen (1984), 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, Y. L." box="[612,753,878,904]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" pagination="167 - 217" refId="ref2427" refString="Chen, Y. L. (1999) Synotis (C. B. Clarke) C. Jeffrey &amp; Y. L. Chen. In: Chen, Y. L. (Ed.) Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae, vol. 77 (1). Science Press, Beijing, pp. 167 - 217." type="book chapter" year="1999">Chen (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, H. M. &amp; Lazkov, G. A. &amp; Illarionova, I. D. &amp; Tong, T. J. &amp; Shao, Y. Y. &amp; Ren, C." box="[808,981,878,904]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref2714" refString="Li, H. M., Lazkov, G. A., Illarionova, I. D., Tong, T. J., Shao, Y. Y. &amp; Ren, C. (2018) Transfer of Senecio karelinioides (AsteraceaeSenecioneae) to Synotis based on evidence from morphology, karyology and ITS / ETS sequence data. Nordic Journal of Botany 32: 1 - 12. [https: // onlinelibrary. wiley. com / doi / abs / 10.1111 / njb. 01838]" type="journal article" year="2018">
Li 
<emphasis box="[840,897,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Clarke" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[992,1073,879,905]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[992,1073,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Synotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is divisible into two well-marked sections, sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Clarke" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[299,380,915,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[299,380,915,941]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Synotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and sect. 
<emphasis box="[493,641,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Karelinioidei</emphasis>
(Fedtschenko &amp; Fedtschenko ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Schischkin, B." box="[1020,1265,914,941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" pagination="699 - 778" refId="ref3052" refString="Schischkin, B. (1961) Senecio L. In: Schischkin, B. &amp; Bobrov, E. G. (Eds.) Flora SSSR, vol. 26. Akademiya Nauk SSSR Publishers, pp. 699 - 778." type="book chapter" year="1961">Schischkin 1961: 751</bibRefCitation>
) Ren 
<emphasis box="[1333,1383,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. in 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, H. M. &amp; Lazkov, G. A. &amp; Illarionova, I. D. &amp; Tong, T. J. &amp; Shao, Y. Y. &amp; Ren, C." pageId="5" pageNumber="283" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref2714" refString="Li, H. M., Lazkov, G. A., Illarionova, I. D., Tong, T. J., Shao, Y. Y. &amp; Ren, C. (2018) Transfer of Senecio karelinioides (AsteraceaeSenecioneae) to Synotis based on evidence from morphology, karyology and ITS / ETS sequence data. Nordic Journal of Botany 32: 1 - 12. [https: // onlinelibrary. wiley. com / doi / abs / 10.1111 / njb. 01838]" type="journal article" year="2018">
Li 
<emphasis box="[136,186,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. (2018: 9)
</bibRefCitation>
. The former is divisible into five not very clearly differentiated series, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1162,1303,950,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunthiana">
<emphasis box="[1162,1303,950,977]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">S. kunthiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonging to 
<emphasis box="[136,176,987,1013]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Syn</emphasis>
. ser. 
<emphasis box="[234,400,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Fulvipapposae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jeffrey, C. &amp; Chen, Y. L." box="[407,717,986,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" pagination="205 - 446" refId="ref2661" refString="Jeffrey, C. &amp; Chen, Y. L. (1984) Taxonomic studies on the tribe Senecioneae (Compositae) of Eastern Asia. Kew Bulletin 39: 205 - 446. [https: // www. jstor. org / stable / 4110124? seq = 1]" type="journal article" year="1984">Jeffrey &amp; Chen (1984: 332)</bibRefCitation>
. Considering the remarkable morphological resemblance between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Ren &amp; Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,328,1022,1049]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyalamensis">
<emphasis box="[136,328,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Syn. nyalamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeffrey &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[383,550,1022,1049]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunthiana">
<emphasis box="[383,550,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Syn. kunthiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we propose to place 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Ren &amp; Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2022" box="[794,986,1022,1049]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Synotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyalamensis">
<emphasis box="[794,986,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Syn. nyalamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also within this series.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
